00:00:00.256 --> 00:00:03.656
<b>You have learned that an end-range wrist motion is low strength</b>

00:00:04.096 --> 00:00:05.120
<b>and high stress.</b>

00:00:05.632 --> 00:00:09.728
<b>And, working with your elbow in the Red Zone increases the force on your body.</b>

00:00:10.240 --> 00:00:12.032
<b>Combine these with a forceful effort,</b>

00:00:12.288 --> 00:00:13.824
<b>and it’s time to stop and think </b>

00:00:14.080 --> 00:00:15.616
<b>“Can I do this a better way?”</b>

00:00:16.384 --> 00:00:16.896
<b>Remember,</b>

00:00:17.152 --> 00:00:18.688
<b>repositioning your work,</b>

00:00:19.200 --> 00:00:20.992
<b>using a better physical technique</b>

00:00:21.248 --> 00:00:22.528
<b>or re-energizing,</b>

00:00:22.784 --> 00:00:25.062
<b>can reduce stress on your hands, wrists,</b>

00:00:25.273 --> 00:00:26.368
<b>elbow and shoulders.</b>

